  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I never accepted it, that they're not going to come back.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I still don't.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After-- I was in Belgium, and I remembered that my parents, at home, always spoke about Israel, which at that time they said Palestine.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because Palestine was the Jewish people's homeland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Zionism, they spoke [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I thought to myself, if my parents died for no reason, let there be a reason to their death, and let their child survive and go on to live in this land of Palestine, which was by then Israel.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And let me become an Israeli citizen, and live there, and be part of-- of what the Jewish people are going to be.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So in '49, I left Belgium with Youth Aliyah, which is the youth movement, you know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I went to Israel, and I lived in Israel.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I went to school in Israel, I went to the Israeli army, and I became an Israeli citizen.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Another language, Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Today I speak Polish, Yiddish, German-- I forgot Czech-- French, English, and Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
